sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K542012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Catechol 2,3-dioxygenase with a C-terminal Arg-tag and Double Terminator (no promoter/RBS)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Made by assembling ([http://partsregistry.org/Part:BBa_K542011 BBa_K542011]) with ([http://partsregistry.org/Part:BBa_B0015 BBa_B0015]).
Arginine tag intended to allow for targeting into Lumazine Synthase microcompartment ([http://partsregistry.org/wiki/index.php?title=Part:BBa_K249002 BBa_K249002]). Eventually plan to produce a construct with the [http://partsregistry.org/wiki/index.php?title=Part:BBa_K542004 microcompartment portion] of the "Co-localizing Construct".
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anthony Vuong
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: ([http://partsregistry.org/Part:BBa_K542011 BBa_K542011]) was assembled by the Lethbridge 2011 team and ([http://partsregistry.org/Part:BBa_B0015 BBa_B0015]) was obtained from iGEM Distribution plates.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Arginine tag intended to allow for targeting into Lumazine Synthase microcompartment ([http://partsregistry.org/wiki/index.php?title=Part:BBa_K249002 BBa_K249002]).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K542011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The xylE gene was PCR'd out of genomic DNA provided by David Lain Houston* with primers adding [http://openwetware.org/wiki/The_BioBricks_Foundation:Standards/Technical/Formats#BBF_RFC_23_.28aka_Biofusion.2C_Silver_lab.29 Silver Lab Biofusion Standard] prefix/suffix. A C-terminal arginine tail was then added ([http://partsregistry.org/wiki/index.php?title=Part:BBa_K249005 BBa_K249005]).
Based on [http://2010.igem.org/Team:Lethbridge/Results#Results_2 characterization on Arg-tagged fluorescent proteins] done by the Lethbridge 2010 team, it was decided that the Arg-tag on xylE would be C-terminal.
*David Lain Houston, PhD Student Institute of Cellular, Molecular, and Systems Biology
Susan Rosser Group Arnott Lab University of Glasgow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
